        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 15 at 4:22PM CDT by NWS Mobile AL</headline>
        <description>At 422 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Gulfcrest, or 6 miles south of Citronelle, moving north at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Satsuma, Citronelle, Chunchula, Gulfcrest, Deer Park, Mount Vernon,
Calvert, and Movico.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
